  All employees of our organisation are required to wear professional clothing.
! Professional clothing is determined by the Cabinet Office.
! Low Ranks are currently required to wear one of the uniform options shown in the UK HQ Lobby.
! The Military Intelligence Branch may set out a specific uniform if made official by the Director General.
! If someone is found not wearing professional clothing,they may bring it to the Cabinet’s attention.
! The offender may then be subject to disciplinary action such as:
! 1. A strike or 2. A court case.
! The Cabinet Office may set out specific time periods where uniform standards are temporarily relaxed.
! Do you have any questions?
  Answer any questions
  
! The Habbo United Kingdom also has a Peerage System, which is decided solely by HM, The King,
! but recommendations are made by the Prime Minister.
  In this system, there are 5 peerages, each with their own requirements and privileges.
  The peerages, in order of honour and nobility (with their eligibility requirements) are as follows:
