*** 31,46 ****
  They are used to recognise UK members for their services to the Sovereign and the organisation.
  There are 4 orders of chivalry and 1 order of merit.
  The five orders, in order of nobility, are as follows:
! 1. Most Noble Order of the Garter 2. Most Honourable Order of the Bath 3. Royal Victorian Order
! 4. Most Excellent Order of the British Empire 5. Order of the Companions of Honour
  
! A knighting ceremony is held by HM, The King in order to give these honours.
! Once knighted, one is able to wear the medal which corresponds with their Order.
  These can be viewed at HabboUK»com under the Learn tab, by clicking Medals and Peerages.
  Additionally, anyone appointed to Order of the Garter may wear the Adorned Fantasy Cape,
! along with the standard HC medal accessory.
  
